adept.kbapi

Class KBEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • adept.kbapi.KBPredicateArgument
      • adept.kbapi.KBRelation
        • adept.kbapi.KBEvent

  • public class KBEvent
extends KBRelation
    Class KBEvent represents Events that have been saved in the KB. This class extends KBRelation, and allows creation of insertion builders from DocumentEvent.
    Author:
    dkolas

      • eventInsertionBuilder

        public static KBEvent.InsertionBuilder eventInsertionBuilder(adept.common.DocumentEvent documentEvent,
                                                             Map<adept.common.Item,KBPredicateArgument> insertedArgumentMap,
                                                             KBOntologyMap ontologyMap)
        Create a new InsertionBuilder from a DocumentEvent. Arguments of the DocumentEvent must have already been inserted into the KB, and the mapping from the DocumentEvent argument targets to the KBPredicateArguments must be provided in the insertedArgumentMap. Provenances in the DocumentEvent will be copied into the builder. Note that if a provenance for the DocumentEvent contains both an EventMention and an EventText, and the scores of those objects are not the same, the score of the EventMention will be used as the KBTextProvenance confidence.
        Parameters:
        documentEvent -
        insertedArgumentMap -
        ontologyMap -
        Returns:

      • eventInsertionBuilder

        public static KBEvent.InsertionBuilder eventInsertionBuilder(adept.common.DocumentRelation documentRelation,
                                                             Map<adept.common.Item,KBPredicateArgument> insertedArgumentMap,
                                                             KBOntologyMap ontologyMap)
        Create a new InsertionBuilder for insertion into the KB. THIS METHOD IS FOR DOCUMENT RELATIONS THAT NEED TO BE CONVERTED INTO AN EVENT. Use KBOntologyMap.relationConvertsToEvent() to know if you need to use this method. This method prepopulates a KBEvent.InsertionBuilder with the content of a DocumentRelation. All argument targets of the DocumentRelation must have been inserted into the KB already, and they must be mapped from an Item to a KBPredicateArgument in the insertedArgumentMap. All provenances on both the DocumentRelation and DocumentRelationArguments will be added to the builder. The ontologyMap will be used to convert Types and Roles from the DocumentRelation into the ontology of the KB. An exception will be thrown if the types cannot be mapped.
        Parameters:
        documentRelation -
        insertedArgumentMap -
        ontologyMap -
        Returns:
